results.name: Number of point-labeled reduced two-graphs with n nodes.
comment: Also number of (n-1)-node labeled mating graphs without isolated nodes, cf. A006024. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Mar 23 2004
link: Michael De Vlieger, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..83
P. J. Cameron, Counting two-graphs related to trees, Elec. J. Combin., Vol. 2, #R4.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} s(n, k) * 2^((k-1) * (k-2) / 2) where s(n, k) are the Stirling numbers of the first kind. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Feb 03 2018
